  "prompt": "Why do I miss him the most at night and have a very bad urge to text him and tell him I miss him?",
  "response": "This is a common emotional experience after a breakup or separation. Several psychological factors contribute to this feeling:\n\n1. Emotional vulnerability\n- Nighttime is quieter and allows more time for reflection\n- Less distractions mean your thoughts can focus on the relationship\n- Feelings of loneliness are often more intense at night\n\n2. Hormonal changes\n- Lower cortisol levels at night can make emotions feel more intense\n- Decreased serotonin can lead to heightened emotional sensitivity\n\n3. Habit and routine\n- You're used to communicating with him during nighttime\n- Previous patterns of sharing your day or saying goodnight create a sense of loss\n\n4. Natural human need for connection\n- Missing emotional intimacy\n- Desire for comfort and familiarity\n\n5. Unresolved emotions\n- Lingering feelings of attachment\n- Potential unfinished emotional business\n\nCoping strategies:\n- Avoid texting impulsively\n- Practice self-care\n- Talk to friends or a therapist\n- Develop new nighttime routines\n- Use journaling to process emotions\n- Practice mindfulness or meditation\n\nRemember, these feelings are normal and will gradually decrease with time and healing.",
